    {
      "type": "h1",
      "content": "A Type Specimen"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "Typography begins with selection. Before spacing, before measure, before any question of hierarchy, a designer must choose which faces will carry the words — this document shows what is available and how each face behaves at text, display, and code sizes."
    },
    {
      "type": "h2",
      "content": "Installed Typefaces"
    },
    {
      "type": "p",
      "content": "Each line below is set in the named face at 11 pt. The sample string exercises numerals, punctuation, and the full latin alphabet run."
    },
    {
      "type": "fontPreview",
      "content": "Arimo: The quick brown fox jumps over 1234567890.",
      "properties": {
        "style": {
          "fontFamily": "Arimo"
        }
      }
    },
